- <i>We'll be cuddling soon</i>
- <i>We'll be cuddling soon</i>

401
00:24:24.741 --> 00:24:27.460
<i>By the silvery moon</i>

402
00:24:39.861 --> 00:24:44.059
Hey, Fred, you don't think Shaggy
could have a crush on Velma, do you?

403
00:24:44.221 --> 00:24:47.338
Not unless she turned into
a steaming bowl of chili cheese fries.

404
00:24:47.501 --> 00:24:48.900
[CHUCKLES]

405
00:24:50.061 --> 00:24:52.291
- Why?
- I don't know, it's just...

406
00:24:52.461 --> 00:24:54.656
...he's been acting really goofy lately.

407
00:24:54.821 --> 00:24:56.413
Even for Shaggy.

408
00:24:56.581 --> 00:24:59.573
And he's been following Velma around
like a puppy dog.

409
00:24:59.741 --> 00:25:02.255
Actually, that would explain
why he's been asking me...

410
00:25:02.421 --> 00:25:04.332
...all those questions about dating.

411
00:25:04.501 --> 00:25:07.095
But I guess he didn't take my advice.

412
00:25:07.261 --> 00:25:09.729
Advice? Wait, Fred, what advice?

413
00:25:14.461 --> 00:25:15.860
[CREATURE GROWLING]

414
00:25:16.701 --> 00:25:21.536
Um, Velma, that wasn't what I thought
it was, was it?

415
00:25:21.701 --> 00:25:22.929
I don't know.

416
00:25:23.101 --> 00:25:27.652
Did you surmise that it was a heretofore
unclassified amphibious humanoid?

417
00:25:28.141 --> 00:25:32.851
No. I thought it was a lake monster!
Zoinks!

418
00:25:33.021 --> 00:25:34.374
Fred?

419
00:25:34.541 --> 00:25:38.011
Exactly what advice
did you give Shaggy about dating?

420
00:25:38.181 --> 00:25:39.170
What?

421
00:25:39.341 --> 00:25:43.380
Oh, you know, just that it's summertime
and we're not really...

422
00:25:43.541 --> 00:25:44.576
[CREATURE ROARS]

423
00:25:44.741 --> 00:25:45.810
Come on.

424
00:25:46.021 --> 00:25:47.852
Go, go, go!

425
00:25:48.061 --> 00:25:50.734
SHAGGY:
It's the lake monster! Save me.

426
00:25:50.941 --> 00:25:53.136
MONSTER:
Ow! My ankle.

427
00:25:53.301 --> 00:25:54.814
What?

428
00:25:58.821 --> 00:25:59.856
UGGINS:
Hey.

429
00:26:00.421 --> 00:26:01.979
Mr. Uggins, I presume?

430
00:26:05.781 --> 00:26:07.339
Call me Elmer.

431
00:26:09.061 --> 00:26:10.335
Hi, kids.

432
00:26:12.781 --> 00:26:16.330
So you've never actually seen
the monster?

433
00:26:16.501 --> 00:26:19.573
I was just using the legend
to make a quick buck.

434
00:26:19.741 --> 00:26:21.891
Made some postcards...

435
00:26:22.101 --> 00:26:24.615
...sold them to the local tourist traps.

436
00:26:25.341 --> 00:26:26.490
- Mm?
- No.

437
00:26:26.661 --> 00:26:28.458
- No.
- Thanks.

438
00:26:29.141 --> 00:26:30.130
Hey, what can I say?

439
00:26:30.301 --> 00:26:32.940
You know, lighthouse keeping
ain't exactly a growth industry.

440
00:26:33.101 --> 00:26:34.580
[CHUCKLING]

441
00:26:35.221 --> 00:26:36.700
Ahem. Anyway...

442
00:26:36.861 --> 00:26:40.331
...when I heard about all the hoopla
down at the country club tonight...

443
00:26:40.501 --> 00:26:44.813
...I figured it might be a good time
to dust off old green-eyes over there...

444
00:26:45.021 --> 00:26:46.500
...and take some new shots.

445
00:26:46.661 --> 00:26:48.174
[IMITATING CAMERA SHUTTER
CLICKING]

446
00:26:48.341 --> 00:26:49.615
But listen, kids...

447
00:26:49.821 --> 00:26:53.211
...if this thing's really back,
you best leave now while you still can.

448
00:26:53.421 --> 00:26:56.299
Come on, you don't really believe
the monster's real, do you?

449
00:26:56.501 --> 00:26:58.856
It's probably some prankster
with a better costume.

450
00:26:59.021 --> 00:27:01.057
Maybe it is and maybe it ain't.

451
00:27:01.221 --> 00:27:03.212
But one thing's for sure...

452
00:27:03.381 --> 00:27:07.010
...the legend is a truly terrible tale.

453
00:27:07.181 --> 00:27:11.459
It all goes back
to the very beginnings of town.

454
00:27:11.661 --> 00:27:14.653
When the first settlers arrived
in these parts...

455
00:27:14.821 --> 00:27:17.494
<i>... they was confronted</i>
<i>by an old woman...</i>

456
00:27:17.661 --> 00:27:20.733
<i>... who was said to live</i>
<i>in a cave by the lake.</i>

457
00:27:20.941 --> 00:27:22.659
Grubwort was her name.

458
00:27:22.861 --> 00:27:24.738
<i>Wanda Grubwort.</i>

459
00:27:24.901 --> 00:27:27.620
<i>She claimed all the land around the lake</i>
<i>belonged to her...</i>

460
00:27:27.781 --> 00:27:30.739
...and told the settlers that
if they didn't turn back...

461
00:27:31.261 --> 00:27:33.297
...they would pay the price.

462
00:27:33.861 --> 00:27:37.217
But them early pioneers was not about
to be turned away so easily...

463
00:27:37.381 --> 00:27:43.058
...so they settled in
and forgot all about her warning.

464
00:27:43.421 --> 00:27:46.811
But Wanda Grubwort did not forget.

465
00:27:46.981 --> 00:27:52.055
And one day,
she fulfilled her dark oath.

466
00:27:53.501 --> 00:27:56.174
<i>Using her magical staff...</i>

467
00:27:56.381 --> 00:28:00.169
<i>... she cast a spell</i>
<i>upon an innocent creature of the lake...</i>

468
00:28:01.021 --> 00:28:05.060
...transforming it into a hideous beast.

469
00:28:09.661 --> 00:28:12.255
<i>Once Grubwort</i>
<i>had her monstrous slave...</i>

470
00:28:12.421 --> 00:28:15.094
<i>... she loosed it upon the villagers.</i>

471
00:28:21.741 --> 00:28:24.619
And then? What happened next?

472
00:28:24.781 --> 00:28:28.615
Well, it's said the settlers
eventually overcame Grubwort...

473
00:28:28.781 --> 00:28:33.332
...tried her for witchery
and burned her at the stake.

474
00:28:36.021 --> 00:28:37.613
Like I said...

475
00:28:38.981 --> 00:28:42.018
...you best leave now
while you still can.

476
00:28:43.501 --> 00:28:46.220
I'm sorry, Mr. Uggins,
but we just don't give up that easy.

477
00:28:47.021 --> 00:28:50.730
He obviously wasn't
in my sophomore geometry class.

478
00:28:52.221 --> 00:28:53.620
[UGGINS GRUNTS]

479
00:28:54.501 --> 00:28:58.574
SHAGGY:
Mr. Shaggy...

480
00:28:59.661 --> 00:29:01.652
...Dinkley.

481
00:29:01.861 --> 00:29:04.216
It's like the angels are singing it.

482
00:29:04.741 --> 00:29:07.130
- Mister...
- Hey, Shagg. What you doing?

483
00:29:08.221 --> 00:29:10.610
Oh! Um... Nothing.

484
00:29:17.381 --> 00:29:21.818
Doctor says I need more linen
in my diet.

485
00:29:22.821 --> 00:29:24.698
Okay. So, have you seen Fred?

486
00:29:25.781 --> 00:29:27.499
He's out on the...

487
00:29:27.701 --> 00:29:30.010
Out on the green,
putting with some girls.

488
00:29:30.821 --> 00:29:31.810
Girls?

489
00:29:31.981 --> 00:29:34.575
FRED:
Now, just remember to follow through.

490
00:29:35.061 --> 00:29:37.052
GIRL 1:
Follow through.

491
00:29:39.101 --> 00:29:40.853
Hey.

492
00:29:41.061 --> 00:29:43.131
GIRL 1: Thanks.
FRED: Okay, guys, I'm out of here.

493
00:29:43.861 --> 00:29:45.977
- Okay, I'll see you guys later.
- Bye.

494
00:29:46.141 --> 00:29:48.496
GIRL 2: Bye, Fred.
FRED: Bye now.

495
00:29:49.901 --> 00:29:51.220
Hey, Daph.

496
00:29:51.421 --> 00:29:53.013
- What's up, Shags?
- Hey, Fred.

497
00:29:56.381 --> 00:29:57.530
What?

498
00:29:57.701 --> 00:29:59.419
Hey, um...

499
00:30:00.181 --> 00:30:02.172
...can I ask your advice
about something?

500
00:30:02.341 --> 00:30:03.694
Sure.

501
00:30:03.901 --> 00:30:05.937
Well, I...

502
00:30:07.141 --> 00:30:09.052
See, I have this friend, okay?

503
00:30:09.221 --> 00:30:12.452
His name's, um, Scruffy. Yeah, Scruffy.
They call him that...

504
00:30:12.621 --> 00:30:15.693
...because he has a goatee.
No, that would be too obvious.

505
00:30:15.901 --> 00:30:21.055
Anyway, so this friend of mine,
who doesn't have a goatee or a dog...

506
00:30:21.261 --> 00:30:23.217
...definitely doesn't have
a dog either...

507
00:30:23.421 --> 00:30:26.777
...he has this crush on this girl
he sometimes solves mysteries with.

508
00:30:26.981 --> 00:30:29.017
No, no. That's a dead giveaway.

509
00:30:29.581 --> 00:30:31.731
- Let me start over. So...
- Shaggy.

510
00:30:32.421 --> 00:30:35.140
It's okay. We know you like Velma.

511
00:30:36.061 --> 00:30:37.050
[SCOFFS]

512
00:30:37.221 --> 00:30:38.449
Oh. Oh, what?

513
00:30:38.621 --> 00:30:40.851
Oh, I don't know
what you guys are talking about.

514
00:30:41.021 --> 00:30:43.296
I definitely do not like... Velma.

515
00:30:43.461 --> 00:30:46.771
You are not gonna believe what I found
in the security footage. Come on.

516
00:30:49.861 --> 00:30:54.059
After you watch this,
I think you'll all be saying "jinkies."

517
00:30:55.341 --> 00:30:58.094
Hey, the security camera
caught the attack.

518
00:30:58.301 --> 00:31:01.452
Yep. And they caught
something else too.

519
00:31:05.301 --> 00:31:08.338
Looks like we have two pranksters
on our hands.

520
00:31:08.541 --> 00:31:09.894
Jinkies.

521
00:31:10.861 --> 00:31:13.056
- Told you.
- Freeze it.

522
00:31:13.221 --> 00:31:16.099
If you zoom in right here,
we can see who's inside that cloak.

523
00:31:21.621 --> 00:31:23.851
SHAGGY:
Oh, look, it's coming into focus.

524
00:31:24.701 --> 00:31:26.293
[SHAGGY SCREAMS]

525
00:31:27.181 --> 00:31:28.614
What happened?

526
00:31:28.781 --> 00:31:31.534
Like, that spooky figure
must be using some sort of magic...

527
00:31:31.701 --> 00:31:33.771
...to prevent us from seeing its face.

528
00:31:33.941 --> 00:31:39.095
I'm afraid the explanation is slightly
less supernatural than that, Shaggy.

529
00:31:39.301 --> 00:31:43.977
I accidentally knocked over my green tea
and short-circuited the hard drive.

530
00:31:44.461 --> 00:31:46.179
- Oh.
- That's okay, Velma.

531
00:31:46.381 --> 00:31:49.578
You know, I'm sure we'll find
another piece of critical evidence.

532
00:31:49.741 --> 00:31:51.140
- Right, guys?
- Yeah, for sure.

533
00:31:51.301 --> 00:31:52.575
- It's groovy.
FRED: Don't worry.

534
00:31:52.781 --> 00:31:55.579
I know this is highly
uncharacteristic behavior.

535
00:31:56.981 --> 00:31:59.256
I'm really sorry, guys.

536
00:32:03.901 --> 00:32:06.415
I'll tender my resignation from the group
if you wish.

537
00:32:06.581 --> 00:32:07.570
- What?
- What?

538
00:32:07.741 --> 00:32:08.730
DAPHNE: Velma.
- Come on.

539
00:32:08.901 --> 00:32:10.459
Velma.

540
00:32:13.021 --> 00:32:14.374
Like, hold on, V.

541
00:32:17.741 --> 00:32:21.939
Don't beat yourself up about this.
You just pulled a Shaggy, that's all.

542
00:32:22.661 --> 00:32:24.299
I do it all the time.

543
00:32:25.421 --> 00:32:28.572
Thanks, Shaggy,
but there's really no excuse.

544
00:32:29.541 --> 00:32:33.500
Maybe reading a little Sylvia Plath
will buoy my spirits.

545
00:32:34.421 --> 00:32:35.774
Hey, I...

546
00:32:35.941 --> 00:32:38.136
I still think you're wonderful.

547
00:32:38.301 --> 00:32:41.259
Shaggy, that was so nice.

548
00:32:41.461 --> 00:32:44.897
That's exactly how you should be
if you're really serious about Velma.

549
00:32:45.261 --> 00:32:47.217
Oh. Oh, what?

550
00:32:47.381 --> 00:32:49.212
Oh, what do you mean?

551
00:32:49.381 --> 00:32:50.814
I do not...

552
00:32:52.101 --> 00:32:53.693
All right, I admit it.

553
00:32:53.861 --> 00:32:55.214
I like Velma.

554
00:32:55.381 --> 00:32:58.453
I'm my friend. I'm Scruffy.

555
00:32:59.981 --> 00:33:01.778
But what am I gonna do?

556
00:33:01.941 --> 00:33:04.455
You know, I don't know
what I'm supposed to say to her.

557
00:33:04.621 --> 00:33:06.498
Let me help you out, Shags.

558
00:33:06.701 --> 00:33:08.339
You gotta be confident, smooth.

559
00:33:08.541 --> 00:33:10.338
- Girls like guys...
- Don't listen to him.

560
00:33:10.501 --> 00:33:12.492
He has no idea what girls like.

561
00:33:12.661 --> 00:33:15.129
See, what girls like is to feel special.

562
00:33:15.301 --> 00:33:17.576
To feel like they're the only one
on a guy's mind.

563
00:33:17.741 --> 00:33:20.016
Yeah, I know that.
But listen, what you wanna do...

564
00:33:20.181 --> 00:33:22.934
Well, if you know that,
then why don't you try it sometime?

565
00:33:23.141 --> 00:33:25.052
What's with you?
Why are you acting weird?

566
00:33:25.221 --> 00:33:27.974
- How exactly am I act...?
- Like, you know what?

567
00:33:28.181 --> 00:33:30.012
Forget I even asked.

568
00:33:30.221 --> 00:33:32.177
I'll just figure this out for myself.

569
00:33:32.341 --> 00:33:36.129
Besides, if I ever get Velma to like me,
I want it to be real...

570
00:33:36.301 --> 00:33:38.735
...not some loosey-goosey thing
like you guys have.

571
00:33:43.021 --> 00:33:45.171
Fred, did you say something
to Shaggy...

572
00:33:45.341 --> 00:33:48.492
...about us having
a "loosey-goosey" relationship?

573
00:33:48.701 --> 00:33:50.692
What? Oh, no, no.

574
00:33:51.421 --> 00:33:53.173
I just told him how we're casual.

575
00:33:53.341 --> 00:33:56.697
You know, how it's summer
and we're just hanging out.

576
00:33:57.461 --> 00:34:00.692
I mean,
that is what we're doing, right?

577
00:34:00.861 --> 00:34:04.774
Yes, Fred.
That is exactly what we're doing.

578
00:34:04.941 --> 00:34:10.573
I'm just so glad
that we're on the same page.

579
00:34:13.221 --> 00:34:17.100
Well, she's not the president
of the drama club for nothing.

580
00:34:18.141 --> 00:34:19.699
I like you, Velma Dinkley.

581
00:34:19.901 --> 00:34:21.300
So, what do you say?

582
00:34:21.501 --> 00:34:24.573
- Will you go on a date with me?
- Sorry, not my type.

583
00:34:24.741 --> 00:34:26.333
Like, come on, Scoob.

584
00:34:26.541 --> 00:34:28.850
Forget Velma.

585
00:34:29.661 --> 00:34:32.539
Time for a midnight snack.

586
00:34:32.981 --> 00:34:35.097
SHAGGY: A what?
- A midnight snack.

587
00:34:35.261 --> 00:34:39.698
You know, a couple of sandwiches,
a rack of ribs, pepperoni?

588
00:34:39.861 --> 00:34:43.615
- What?
- Oh, just follow me. Whew.

589
00:34:44.301 --> 00:34:45.370
Just my luck.

590
00:34:45.541 --> 00:34:49.011
I've got a talking dog
and I can't understand a word he says.

591
00:35:06.701 --> 00:35:08.692
SHAGGY:
Mm, mm, mm.

592
00:35:08.941 --> 00:35:11.774
Sandwich, look out.

593
00:35:13.501 --> 00:35:15.412
[SNIFFS THEN SIGHS]

594
00:35:15.581 --> 00:35:17.219
Is that Eau de' Dinkley I detect?

595
00:35:19.181 --> 00:35:20.330
Shaggy?

596
00:35:20.501 --> 00:35:24.938
Shaggy? Hey, what about
my midnight snack?

597
00:35:25.101 --> 00:35:27.092
[GROWLS]

598
00:35:28.621 --> 00:35:29.849
Huh.

599
00:35:30.261 --> 00:35:31.933
DAPHNE:
Nice shot.

600
00:35:43.741 --> 00:35:45.379
Mine.

601
00:35:45.581 --> 00:35:47.014
[MAN GRUNTS
AND DAPHNE SHRIEKS]

602
00:35:59.781 --> 00:36:01.737
Velma?

603
00:36:04.621 --> 00:36:06.737
Where is she?

604
00:36:13.461 --> 00:36:14.450
[TWIG CRACKS]

605
00:36:14.621 --> 00:36:16.020
[SIGHS]

606
00:36:19.861 --> 00:36:22.295
Oh, Velma, is that you?

607
00:36:25.581 --> 00:36:26.570
[ROARS]

608
00:36:26.941 --> 00:36:28.090
[SCREAMS]

609
00:36:31.381 --> 00:36:32.370
Oh, hi, Fred.

610
00:36:34.181 --> 00:36:35.455
Is something wrong?

611
00:36:35.661 --> 00:36:37.333
SHAGGY:
Help!

612
00:36:37.501 --> 00:36:39.696
- Help, help!
- Come on.

613
00:36:40.701 --> 00:36:41.929
- Shaggy.
- Aah!

614
00:36:42.101 --> 00:36:43.693
- What's wrong?
- Oh.

615
00:36:43.861 --> 00:36:45.453
Oh, you know, nothing.

616
00:36:45.621 --> 00:36:48.010
I just thought I'd work
on my blood-curdling scream.

617
00:36:48.181 --> 00:36:50.900
What the heck do you think is wrong?
It's the lake monster.

618
00:36:51.381 --> 00:36:52.370
Whoa!

619
00:36:54.101 --> 00:36:57.218
That's it, time to unmask this prankster
once and for all.

620
00:36:57.421 --> 00:36:59.412
[GRUNTING]

621
00:37:00.221 --> 00:37:02.735
Come on, help me with this mask.

622
00:37:06.141 --> 00:37:08.416
Fred, I don't think this thing
is a mask.

623
00:37:12.021 --> 00:37:14.774
Ew! Gross.

624
00:37:15.301 --> 00:37:17.178
FRED:
Keep moving.

625
00:37:19.421 --> 00:37:21.491
This thing keeps getting
the jump on us.

626
00:37:21.661 --> 00:37:24.619
It can't jump in two directions.
Come on, split up.

627
00:37:29.781 --> 00:37:31.339
Like, why did he have to pick me?

628
00:37:31.501 --> 00:37:34.334
In gym class,
I'm always the last one picked.

629
00:37:35.021 --> 00:37:36.010
Huh. Heh.

630
00:37:36.181 --> 00:37:37.773
Oh, zoinks.

631
00:37:37.941 --> 00:37:40.057
[ROARING]

632
00:37:43.981 --> 00:37:45.892
SCOOBY:
I'll save you, Shaggy.

633
00:37:49.381 --> 00:37:50.416
SHAGGY:
Like, thanks, buddy.

634
00:37:50.581 --> 00:37:53.175
I thought that giant mutant frog
was gonna make me croak.

635
00:37:53.381 --> 00:37:54.370
[SHAGGY GIGGLES]

636
00:37:54.541 --> 00:37:57.374
Oh, boy, I wish I could enjoy that one.

637
00:37:59.261 --> 00:38:01.695
Oh, heh. Oh. You did it, boy.

638
00:38:02.261 --> 00:38:03.455
Oh, what a friend.

639
00:38:03.621 --> 00:38:04.974
What a pal.

640
00:38:05.141 --> 00:38:06.176
What a sand trap.

641
00:38:06.581 --> 00:38:08.572
[BOTH SCREAMING]

642
00:38:14.581 --> 00:38:17.937
Oh, boy, Scoob.
I owe you one, buddy.

643
00:38:18.101 --> 00:38:20.615
If it wasn't for you, I would...

644
00:38:20.821 --> 00:38:23.381
Hey, would you look at that?

645
00:38:26.261 --> 00:38:28.377
- It's one of those moonstones.
- Yeah.

646
00:38:28.541 --> 00:38:31.977
Velma loves these things almost
as much I love deep-fried...

647
00:38:32.141 --> 00:38:33.859
Well, anything. Huh.

648
00:38:34.061 --> 00:38:35.733
Groovy.

649
00:38:36.021 --> 00:38:37.693
Huh? Hmph.

650
00:38:37.861 --> 00:38:40.659
Velma, Velma, Velma. Pfft.

651
00:38:43.581 --> 00:38:46.254
Hey, come on,
I think the coast is clear.

652
00:38:47.101 --> 00:38:50.093
This doesn't make sense.
There's no such thing as a lake monster.

653
00:38:50.261 --> 00:38:53.697
Tell that to the thing
that just threw up an aquarium.

654
00:38:53.981 --> 00:38:56.814
So now do you wanna tell me
who those guys were?

655
00:38:56.981 --> 00:38:58.300
Not now, Fred.

656
00:39:00.141 --> 00:39:02.132
[MONSTER GROWLING]

657
00:39:06.941 --> 00:39:09.660
Oh, that was worse than my date
with Herbie Zimmer.

658
00:39:09.861 --> 00:39:12.534
Totally, I... Wait, you went on a date
with Herbie Zi...?

659
00:39:13.541 --> 00:39:15.532
[MONSTER SCREAMING]

660
00:39:27.461 --> 00:39:28.655
WOMAN:
Creature.

661
00:39:29.421 --> 00:39:32.458
What are you doing?
You're supposed to be searching.

662
00:39:32.621 --> 00:39:34.612
With all the bedlam
you've raised tonight...

663
00:39:34.781 --> 00:39:36.499
...we'll have to stop early.

664
00:39:36.661 --> 00:39:38.014
Return to the lake.

665
00:39:38.181 --> 00:39:41.651
I'll summon you
when it's safe to resume our search.

666
00:39:51.061 --> 00:39:52.289
[DAPHNE SIGHS]

667
00:39:52.821 --> 00:39:55.096
- That was close.
- Yeah.

668
00:39:56.901 --> 00:39:59.540
Hey. Not bad.

669
00:39:59.741 --> 00:40:01.140
[SIGHS]

670
00:40:01.981 --> 00:40:03.937
Uncle Thorny.

671
00:40:04.741 --> 00:40:06.015
That thing came back.

672
00:40:06.181 --> 00:40:08.376
Oh, you think?

673
00:40:10.141 --> 00:40:13.372
Canceled memberships
and now all this damage.

674
00:40:14.101 --> 00:40:17.696
I hate to say it, I may have no choice
but to shut this place down...

675
00:40:17.861 --> 00:40:21.297
...and go back to my life
as an international playboy.

676
00:40:24.221 --> 00:40:25.290
SHAGGY:
Hey, guys.

677
00:40:25.501 --> 00:40:26.934
Shaggy, you're okay.

678
00:40:27.101 --> 00:40:30.616
Well, yeah, I am,
but has anyone seen Velma?

679
00:40:30.781 --> 00:40:33.818
Before the monster attacked,
she was out here, I know it.

680
00:40:33.981 --> 00:40:35.050
Oh, no.

681
00:40:35.221 --> 00:40:37.781
Oh, you don't think the lake monster
got to her, do you?

682
00:40:37.941 --> 00:40:40.614
I've seen monster movies,
I know how this works.

683
00:40:40.781 --> 00:40:42.453
[ROARS THEN SCREAMS]

684
00:40:42.621 --> 00:40:45.499
Shaggy, Shaggy. Calm down, okay?

685
00:40:45.661 --> 00:40:46.935
- We're gonna find her.
- Yeah.

686
00:40:47.101 --> 00:40:48.090
- Let's go.
SHAGGY: Okay.

687
00:40:48.261 --> 00:40:50.695
FRED:
Velma!

688
00:40:52.381 --> 00:40:54.133
DAPHNE:
Velma!

689
00:40:54.301 --> 00:40:55.814
Velma?

690
00:40:55.981 --> 00:40:56.970
Where are you?

691
00:40:57.141 --> 00:40:59.894
- Velma!
- Velma!

692
00:41:01.701 --> 00:41:04.340
Hey, guys, I found her.

693
00:41:09.341 --> 00:41:12.492
- Oh, no. She's dead.
- Oh!

694
00:41:12.661 --> 00:41:15.129
Oh, she looks so peaceful.

695
00:41:15.301 --> 00:41:17.690
Oh, I can't look.

696
00:41:18.101 --> 00:41:19.170
[GROANS]

697
00:41:19.661 --> 00:41:21.970
Uh... Guys?

698
00:41:24.621 --> 00:41:27.374
- What's going on?
- Oh, it's a miracle.

699
00:41:27.541 --> 00:41:30.055
FRED: What happened to you
last night, Velma?

700
00:41:30.461 --> 00:41:32.019
I don't know.

701
00:41:32.901 --> 00:41:36.371
I couldn't sleep,
so I went for a walk by the lake.

702
00:41:36.821 --> 00:41:38.937
But then that fog rolled in and...

703
00:41:40.141 --> 00:41:43.292
Well, I must have gotten lost.

704
00:41:43.461 --> 00:41:45.929
I sat down to wait until it lifted...

705
00:41:46.141 --> 00:41:48.291
...and I must have fallen asleep.

706
00:41:48.741 --> 00:41:51.050
Don't you ever do that to us again,
you hear?

707
00:41:51.221 --> 00:41:54.054
You had us all worried so...
What are those?

708
00:41:56.781 --> 00:41:59.534
- They kind of look like warts.
- Warts?

709
00:41:59.701 --> 00:42:01.214
Egads.

710
00:42:01.381 --> 00:42:03.178
Oh, no.

711
00:42:03.341 --> 00:42:08.938
I'm sure it's just some kind
of urushiol-induced dermatitis.

712
00:42:09.101 --> 00:42:11.012
- Oh.
- Yeah.

713
00:42:12.101 --> 00:42:15.093
Anyway, what's going on?

714
00:42:15.261 --> 00:42:18.333
You missed another attack.
Come on, we'll get you cleaned up...

715
00:42:18.501 --> 00:42:21.140
...and we'll fill you in.
VELMA: Another attack?

716
00:42:21.301 --> 00:42:23.974
Anybody else hungry? I know I am.

717
00:42:24.141 --> 00:42:25.210
Shocking.

718
00:42:25.421 --> 00:42:26.820
Mm.

719
00:42:27.501 --> 00:42:28.490
Ooh.

720
00:42:28.661 --> 00:42:31.380
So you think the monster's real
and someone's using it...

721
00:42:31.541 --> 00:42:32.974
...to dig up something
on the grounds?

722
00:42:33.141 --> 00:42:36.292
Yeah. Problem is, we don't have
a single clue about who's using it.

723
00:42:36.501 --> 00:42:41.416
Yes, we do. The mysterious figure
had a streak of purple paint on its cloak.

724
00:42:42.741 --> 00:42:45.539
- So?
- So remember the boat that we passed...

725
00:42:45.701 --> 00:42:48.852
...on the way up here?
Shaggy called it the <i>S.S. Daphne.</i>

726
00:42:49.021 --> 00:42:51.216
It was being painted
the exact same color.

727
00:42:51.421 --> 00:42:55.699
I'd be willing to bet that whoever's
behind this has been on that boat.

728
00:42:55.901 --> 00:42:57.892
All right, gang,
we know what we have to do.

729
00:42:58.341 --> 00:43:01.777
After our shifts tonight, we'll head
to the docks and we'll check it out.

730
00:43:03.941 --> 00:43:04.930
No.

731
00:43:07.501 --> 00:43:09.059
No.

732
00:43:09.501 --> 00:43:12.015
I'm not going
until I do what I've been trying to do...

733
00:43:12.181 --> 00:43:14.092
...since we first got here.

734
00:43:16.701 --> 00:43:21.217
Um, Velma, I learned something today.

735
00:43:21.381 --> 00:43:23.815
Life is like a chocolate soufflé.

736
00:43:24.501 --> 00:43:28.619
And if you wait too long to dig in,
it could just collapse on you.

737
00:43:29.261 --> 00:43:33.254
So anyway,
what I'm trying to say is...

738
00:43:37.621 --> 00:43:41.091
...Velma Dinkley,
will you go on a date with me?

739
00:43:42.141 --> 00:43:44.575
- Heh. A date?
- Yeah.

740
00:43:45.581 --> 00:43:47.333
Shaggy.

741
00:43:48.541 --> 00:43:50.133
Are you serious?

742
00:43:50.301 --> 00:43:53.976
I've never been more serious
about anything in my entire life.

743
00:43:54.181 --> 00:43:57.696
Except maybe dinosaurs,
but that was a long time ago.

744
00:43:58.861 --> 00:44:02.649
Shaggy, that's very sweet of you...

745
00:44:03.541 --> 00:44:06.931
...but we're right in the middle
of an investigation.

746
00:44:07.821 --> 00:44:10.733
Well, like,
I think Fred and Daphne can handle it.

747
00:44:10.941 --> 00:44:14.411
They probably wanna spend some
quality time together anyway, right?

748
00:44:14.581 --> 00:44:16.173
- No, not really.
- I'm good.

749
00:44:17.221 --> 00:44:19.496
I don't know, Shaggy.

750
00:44:19.661 --> 00:44:20.696
SHAGGY:
Oh.

751
00:44:22.021 --> 00:44:24.376
Like... Like, yeah, that's...

752
00:44:24.541 --> 00:44:25.769
I mean, that's fine.

753
00:44:25.981 --> 00:44:27.255
I...

754
00:44:27.821 --> 00:44:30.381
If I were you, I probably
wouldn't wanna go on a date...

755
00:44:30.541 --> 00:44:32.736
...with a goofy guy
like me either so...

756
00:44:37.941 --> 00:44:39.738
Hold on.

757
00:44:40.421 --> 00:44:42.173
Shaggy, you know what?

758
00:44:42.861 --> 00:44:45.216
I will go on a date with you tonight.

759
00:44:45.781 --> 00:44:46.770
Oh, really?

760
00:44:48.141 --> 00:44:49.972
- You mean it?
- Sure.

761
00:44:50.141 --> 00:44:51.130
Why not?

762
00:44:51.341 --> 00:44:53.377
Yes.

763
00:44:53.901 --> 00:44:55.414
Pick you up around 7.

764
00:44:57.061 --> 00:44:58.460
[GRUNTS]

765
00:44:59.021 --> 00:45:00.056
Seven o'clock.

766
00:45:03.621 --> 00:45:05.054
Slippery.

767
00:45:05.901 --> 00:45:06.890
[PIANO CRASHES]

768
00:45:07.061 --> 00:45:08.574
- Ouch.
SHAGGY: I'm okay.

769
00:45:11.941 --> 00:45:14.011
Oh, curse this mop top.

770
00:45:14.181 --> 00:45:16.741
I can't do anything with it.

771
00:45:19.141 --> 00:45:21.496
Okay, Scoob, how do I look?

772
00:45:21.661 --> 00:45:23.731
Ah. Handsome as a devil.

773
00:45:23.901 --> 00:45:26.290
What about me?

774
00:45:26.701 --> 00:45:28.054
Oh. Um...

775
00:45:28.221 --> 00:45:30.177
Like, as dapper as a Dalmatian...

776
00:45:30.341 --> 00:45:34.698
...but where are you headed, buddy?
- With you. Where else?

777
00:45:34.901 --> 00:45:38.371
Oh, um, heh. Um...

778
00:45:38.581 --> 00:45:41.049
You know, buddy...

779
00:45:41.221 --> 00:45:44.816
...I'm gonna have to fly solo
on this one tonight.

780
00:45:44.981 --> 00:45:47.620
- Solo?
- Yeah, you know, like...

781
00:45:47.781 --> 00:45:50.978
...you're just gonna have to do
your own thing, you know what I mean?

782
00:45:51.141 --> 00:45:54.929
My own thing? But, Shaggy...

783
00:45:55.101 --> 00:45:58.138
Thanks for understanding, Scoob.

784
00:45:58.981 --> 00:46:00.255
[SIGHS]

785
00:46:00.421 --> 00:46:02.218
I'll see you later, pal.

786
00:46:02.381 --> 00:46:05.054
Goodbye, Shaggy.

787
00:46:05.221 --> 00:46:07.212
[CRYING]

788
00:46:17.661 --> 00:46:19.538
[SHAGGY WHIMPERING]

789
00:46:19.701 --> 00:46:23.011
Who's the best puppy
in the whole wide world?

790
00:46:24.501 --> 00:46:26.492
[CONTINUES WHIMPERING]

791
00:46:28.181 --> 00:46:31.935
No. No more rolling over.

792
00:46:44.861 --> 00:46:45.976
- Ready?
- Yeah.

793
00:46:46.141 --> 00:46:48.257
Good. So...

794
00:46:48.421 --> 00:46:49.979
...who were they?

795
00:46:50.141 --> 00:46:51.813
Who were who?

796
00:46:52.621 --> 00:46:53.656
Oh, ho.

797
00:46:53.821 --> 00:46:57.530
Are you still wondering about those boys
I was playing tennis with?

798
00:46:57.701 --> 00:47:00.295
They were nobody, Fred.
Just some caddies I met.

799
00:47:00.461 --> 00:47:01.860
Why?

800
00:47:02.341 --> 00:47:03.774
You're not jealous, are you?

801
00:47:03.941 --> 00:47:06.171
Jealous? No, no.

802
00:47:06.341 --> 00:47:08.093
I'm not jealous. No way.

803
00:47:08.261 --> 00:47:10.252
I don't get jealous.

804
00:47:10.421 --> 00:47:12.173
Yeah, right.

805
00:47:26.181 --> 00:47:27.580
[SNIFFING]

806
00:47:31.621 --> 00:47:34.089
- Good evening, Norville.
- Heh.

807
00:47:34.541 --> 00:47:35.940
[CHUCKLES]

808
00:47:36.581 --> 00:47:38.173
Shaggy.

809
00:47:39.021 --> 00:47:40.693
Aren't you gonna say anything?

810
00:47:43.821 --> 00:47:46.893
I like corn dogs.

811
00:47:53.661 --> 00:47:56.016
- Thanks, Shaggy.
- Yeah.

812
00:47:59.501 --> 00:48:01.014
Thank you.

813
00:48:01.821 --> 00:48:03.777
Oh. Ahem.

814
00:48:15.821 --> 00:48:17.015
[CLEARS THROAT]

815
00:48:19.021 --> 00:48:21.819
Well, it looks like we got
the whole place to ourselves.

816
00:48:22.021 --> 00:48:27.015
Yes, unfortunately, that only emphasizes
the urgency of our investigation.

817
00:48:27.221 --> 00:48:29.815
- Sure we shouldn't check with Fred...?
- Oh, come on, V.

818
00:48:29.981 --> 00:48:33.451
Like, just try to put those frontal lobes
on the back burner tonight, okay?

819
00:48:34.741 --> 00:48:36.413
Okay, Shaggy.

820
00:48:36.581 --> 00:48:40.335
I must admit, I do have a hard time
letting myself relax.

821
00:48:40.541 --> 00:48:42.418
Especially recently.

822
00:48:42.621 --> 00:48:46.136
Ever since we've been here,
I just haven't felt like myself.

823
00:48:48.541 --> 00:48:51.419
Well, whoever you are, I like it.

824
00:48:53.341 --> 00:48:54.490
Thanks, Shaggy.

825
00:48:56.701 --> 00:48:57.975
Oh. Um...

826
00:48:58.141 --> 00:49:02.214
Now, come on,
I want this night to be perfect.

827
00:49:03.021 --> 00:49:04.420
[SCREAMS]

828
00:49:05.501 --> 00:49:06.536
Velma.

829
00:49:07.821 --> 00:49:09.539
VELMA:
My glasses.

830
00:49:09.701 --> 00:49:10.975
Here, let me help you up.

831
00:49:11.141 --> 00:49:12.210
Are you okay?

832
00:49:12.381 --> 00:49:13.734
I'm sorry, I...

833
00:49:13.901 --> 00:49:16.415
I don't know what came over me.

834
00:49:17.101 --> 00:49:18.739
Oh, here. Here you go.

835
00:49:18.901 --> 00:49:20.095
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

836
00:49:23.701 --> 00:49:26.773
Oh, boy.
Here, let me get you some water.

837
00:49:26.981 --> 00:49:30.451
<i>Garçon,</i> water, please.

838
00:49:30.941 --> 00:49:32.897
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

839
00:49:33.101 --> 00:49:34.090
[LAUGHING]

840
00:49:35.021 --> 00:49:36.818
[HUMMING]

841
00:49:41.661 --> 00:49:42.650
[SCOOBY BELCHES]

842
00:49:42.821 --> 00:49:44.015
[SCOOBY SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

843
00:49:44.861 --> 00:49:48.217
Oh, whoops.
I seem to have dropped my fork.

844
00:49:48.941 --> 00:49:51.501
Here, help me find it, waiter.

845
00:49:52.661 --> 00:49:54.299
Scooby-Doo, what are you doing?

846
00:49:54.461 --> 00:49:57.453
Waiting tables. Fresh ground pepper?

847
00:49:57.621 --> 00:50:00.419
Scooby, get out of here, buddy.
You're gonna ruin everything.

848
00:50:00.581 --> 00:50:02.253
No.

849
00:50:02.741 --> 00:50:07.019
Okay, but would you do it
for a Scooby snack?

850
00:50:07.181 --> 00:50:09.900
I can't be bought. Hmph.

851
00:50:10.741 --> 00:50:11.890
Now, you listen, Scoob...

852
00:50:12.061 --> 00:50:14.939
...I'm the master and I command you
to go back to your room...

853
00:50:15.101 --> 00:50:18.059
...and quit being such a bad dog.

854
00:50:19.901 --> 00:50:21.254
Puppy loving...

855
00:50:21.461 --> 00:50:23.452
[SCOOBY MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY]

856
00:50:24.421 --> 00:50:26.218
Bad dog? Huh.

857
00:50:26.421 --> 00:50:28.616
I'll show you a bad dog.

858
00:50:28.901 --> 00:50:31.017
[LAUGHS THEN GROWLS]

859
00:50:31.421 --> 00:50:33.377
No, Shaggy, don't.
The waiter will bring...

860
00:50:33.541 --> 00:50:34.815
[SCREAMS]

861
00:50:36.101 --> 00:50:37.773
Would you care to hear our specials?

862
00:50:37.941 --> 00:50:40.011
Scooby-Doo? Is that you?

863
00:50:40.221 --> 00:50:41.973
I didn't invite him.

864
00:50:42.181 --> 00:50:45.218
He just showed up
and tried to sabotage everything and...

865
00:50:45.381 --> 00:50:47.611
- And...
- Is that what I think it is?

866
00:50:49.821 --> 00:50:51.015
Oh, uh, heh.

867
00:50:51.181 --> 00:50:54.537
Yeah, that was supposed to be
a surprise.

868
00:50:54.741 --> 00:50:56.811
I found it in a sand trap last night.

869
00:50:57.021 --> 00:50:59.660
It's one of those moonstones, right?

870
00:51:00.221 --> 00:51:01.210
Yes.

871
00:51:01.421 --> 00:51:05.255
I was gonna give it to you when I walked
you back to your room tonight, but...

872
00:51:05.421 --> 00:51:07.491
It's beautiful.

873
00:51:09.541 --> 00:51:12.055
Excuse me, I have to go now.

874
00:51:12.701 --> 00:51:15.659
Wait, what? Well, Velma...

875
00:51:18.141 --> 00:51:19.893
This is all your fault, Scooby-Doo.

876
00:51:20.061 --> 00:51:21.858
You ruined everything.

877
00:51:22.021 --> 00:51:24.535
No, I didn't.

878
00:51:24.701 --> 00:51:26.100
[SCOOBY GROWLS]

879
00:51:35.021 --> 00:51:37.535
DAPHNE:
There it is, the purple boat.

880
00:51:37.701 --> 00:51:39.771
FRED:
She. There she is.

881
00:51:39.981 --> 00:51:41.334
A boat is a she, like a girl.

882
00:51:41.501 --> 00:51:43.571
But not one who goes around
playing tennis...

883
00:51:43.741 --> 00:51:46.096
...with every boy boat in the harbor.

884
00:51:55.741 --> 00:51:58.016
That cloaked figure
was definitely here.

885
00:51:58.181 --> 00:52:00.251
All hands on deck.

886
00:52:21.221 --> 00:52:23.781
Fred, look.

887
00:52:34.101 --> 00:52:36.137
- Ladies first.
- Mm-mm.

888
00:52:36.301 --> 00:52:37.734
Fine.

889
00:53:18.461 --> 00:53:20.895
Looks like a bunch of old newspapers.

890
00:53:21.061 --> 00:53:22.255
DAPHNE:
I'll say.

891
00:53:22.501 --> 00:53:23.900
FRED:
Huh.

892
00:53:25.181 --> 00:53:29.891
Hey, these are about that witch
from Uggins' story, Wanda Grubwort.

893
00:53:30.061 --> 00:53:32.859
DAPHNE: Evil staff?
- Yeah, remember? Didn't Elmer say...

894
00:53:33.021 --> 00:53:35.899
...an ancient staff was the source
of her black magic?

895
00:53:37.981 --> 00:53:39.573
DAPHNE:
Hey, look at this one.

896
00:53:41.541 --> 00:53:45.659
That must be what the monster's doing,
looking for the source of her powers.

897
00:53:45.821 --> 00:53:48.893
The problem is we still don't know
who's controlling it.

898
00:53:49.821 --> 00:53:52.415
Wait a second, maybe we do.

899
00:53:54.381 --> 00:53:57.930
Wanda Grubwort had children. She could
still have descendants living in town.

900
00:53:58.101 --> 00:53:59.295
Maybe one got angry...

901
00:53:59.461 --> 00:54:02.498
...when your uncle built on their land
and decided to get revenge.

902
00:54:05.141 --> 00:54:06.859
What was that?

903
00:54:09.501 --> 00:54:11.731
It's locked. Hello!

904
00:54:11.941 --> 00:54:13.579
Help. Help.

905
00:54:13.741 --> 00:54:17.177
DAPHNE:
Anyone out there? Let us out.

906
00:54:19.501 --> 00:54:20.536
Help. Help.

907
00:54:20.701 --> 00:54:22.896
Is anyone out there? Oh, great.

908
00:54:23.061 --> 00:54:25.291
If we don't get this open,
we'll be stuck here all night.

909
00:54:25.461 --> 00:54:26.894
[RUMBLING]

910
00:54:27.941 --> 00:54:29.693
That might be the least
of our worries.

911
00:54:30.581 --> 00:54:31.900
- Hello!
- Is anyone out there?

912
00:54:32.061 --> 00:54:33.050
Help!

913
00:54:33.901 --> 00:54:36.096
- Help, help!
DAPHNE: We need to get out.

914
00:54:36.261 --> 00:54:37.899
FRED: Help, anybody.
DAPHNE: Anyone!

915
00:54:38.101 --> 00:54:40.774
FRED: Help, anybody!
- Help, get us out!

916
00:54:40.941 --> 00:54:43.136
FRED:
Help, help, anybody!

917
00:54:43.341 --> 00:54:46.651
- Help, help.
- We're stuck, it's filling.

918
00:54:47.461 --> 00:54:50.055
Fred, you need to do something.
We're gonna drown.

919
00:54:50.261 --> 00:54:54.049
I have an idea. Why don't we call
those guys you were playing tennis with?

920
00:54:54.221 --> 00:54:57.816
- I knew it, you are jealous.
- Yeah, maybe I am.

921
00:54:57.981 --> 00:55:01.212
- Good, that was the point.
- You were just lying to make me jealous?

922
00:55:01.381 --> 00:55:04.691
Yes, I'm trying to pay you back
for playing golf with those floozies.

923
00:55:04.861 --> 00:55:06.977
Flooz...? Oh, that was different.

924
00:55:07.141 --> 00:55:09.097
How? How was that any different?

925
00:55:09.261 --> 00:55:11.491
I don't know, they were... It just was.

926
00:55:11.661 --> 00:55:13.253
All right, you know what, Fred?

927
00:55:13.421 --> 00:55:16.618
If I'm gonna die,
I don't want to die dating a jerk.

928
00:55:16.781 --> 00:55:20.296
Yeah, well, if I'm gonna die,
I don't want to die dating a sneaky...

929
00:55:20.941 --> 00:55:23.660
...manipulative, game-playing...

930
00:55:28.981 --> 00:55:31.290
You see that? I saved us.

931
00:55:31.461 --> 00:55:34.771
That's lovely,
but we're still broken up.

932
00:55:34.941 --> 00:55:35.930
What?

933
00:55:36.141 --> 00:55:37.779
Good.

934
00:55:38.461 --> 00:55:40.452
[MUTTERING]

935
00:56:02.581 --> 00:56:04.299
Like, what happened to you guys?

936
00:56:04.501 --> 00:56:05.775
What happened?

937
00:56:05.941 --> 00:56:07.533
We broke up, that's what happened.

938
00:56:07.741 --> 00:56:09.857
Yeah, best decision I ever made too.

939
00:56:10.061 --> 00:56:12.450
Did you just say best decision
you ever made?

940
00:56:12.621 --> 00:56:15.055
That's funny,
because I broke up with you.

941
00:56:15.221 --> 00:56:16.210
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

942
00:56:16.381 --> 00:56:18.019
What? You did not.

943
00:56:18.181 --> 00:56:19.819
- Guys?
DAPHNE: I did so.

944
00:56:19.981 --> 00:56:21.573
Guys.

945
00:56:21.781 --> 00:56:26.901
That's a real bummer and all,
but I kind of meant, why are you wet?

946
00:56:27.221 --> 00:56:28.654
Oh, that.

947
00:56:28.821 --> 00:56:31.699
Well, let's just say we almost got in
over our heads.

948
00:56:31.861 --> 00:56:34.819
But we figured out
that Wanda Grubwort's descendant...

949
00:56:34.981 --> 00:56:38.610
...might be trying to reconstruct
her magical staff.

950
00:56:41.461 --> 00:56:44.897
Hey, how'd it go with Velma?

951
00:56:46.221 --> 00:56:49.372
Yeah. Ask my waiter.

952
00:56:49.581 --> 00:56:51.856
DAPHNE:
Grubek, Grubel, Guzzak.

953
00:56:52.621 --> 00:56:53.610
No Grubwort.

954
00:56:54.261 --> 00:56:58.857
Huh. Would you look at that.
What a crazy coincidence.

955
00:56:59.861 --> 00:57:01.817
What's that, Shags?

956
00:57:02.261 --> 00:57:06.174
Oh. Remember that creepy general store
we stopped at on the way in?

957
00:57:06.701 --> 00:57:08.737
It was called Trowburgs.

958
00:57:08.901 --> 00:57:13.258
Well, if you spell Trowburg backwards
you get Grubwort.

959
00:57:13.461 --> 00:57:14.735
What are the odds, huh?

960
00:57:14.901 --> 00:57:18.291
Excuse me,
you are on my side of the room.

961
00:57:27.701 --> 00:57:29.100
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY GULP]

962
00:57:41.461 --> 00:57:42.689
[THUNDER CRASHING]

963
00:57:44.421 --> 00:57:46.298
There. Shaggy, Scooby,
go around back.

964
00:57:46.461 --> 00:57:48.691
- I'm not going with him.
- I'm not going with him.

965
00:57:48.861 --> 00:57:51.216
- You think I want to go with you?
SHAGGY: Seriously...

966
00:57:51.381 --> 00:57:53.053
SCOOBY: I'm not going with Shaggy.
FRED: Enough.

967
00:57:53.221 --> 00:57:55.291
- Guys, let's just go.
- Go.

968
00:57:59.141 --> 00:58:00.813
- Surprise.
WOMAN: Oh, no.

969
00:58:00.981 --> 00:58:02.334
[WOMAN CACKLING]

970
00:58:02.501 --> 00:58:04.093
Come on.

971
00:58:04.781 --> 00:58:06.180
Hey, wait for me.

972
00:58:15.941 --> 00:58:17.579
In here.

973
00:58:25.301 --> 00:58:27.019
SCOOBY:
This way.

974
00:58:27.741 --> 00:58:29.333
The other way.

975
00:58:34.221 --> 00:58:35.620
[SHAGGY SCREAMING]

976
00:58:38.661 --> 00:58:39.650
No.

977
00:58:41.341 --> 00:58:43.855
FRED: Come on.
SHAGGY: No, please.

978
00:58:44.021 --> 00:58:45.500
Please.

979
00:58:51.981 --> 00:58:54.051
- Now can we split up?
- Ugh.

980
00:58:58.901 --> 00:59:01.369
SHAGGY: Hey, come on, Scoob.
- I'm right behind you, Shaggy.

981
00:59:01.541 --> 00:59:03.532
[SHAGGY SCREAMS]

982
00:59:04.061 --> 00:59:06.177
Change of plans.

983
00:59:09.501 --> 00:59:12.299
WOMAN:
And stay out.

984
00:59:14.981 --> 00:59:18.018
Time to unmask
the person behind this mystery.

985
00:59:19.661 --> 00:59:22.255
- It's you?
- What?

986
00:59:22.421 --> 00:59:24.537
Like, it can't be.

987
00:59:26.781 --> 00:59:27.975
Velma?

988
00:59:28.901 --> 00:59:32.098
[IN DISTORTED VOICE]
Oh, you fools. I'm not Velma.

989
00:59:33.101 --> 00:59:34.454
[DAPHNE SCREAMS]

990
00:59:34.621 --> 00:59:36.418
Daphne.

991
00:59:37.861 --> 00:59:39.852
I don't want to hurt you, Velma.

992
00:59:40.061 --> 00:59:42.621
Oh, but I do want to hurt you,
pretty boy.

993
00:59:44.101 --> 00:59:45.534
Sorry, Velma.

994
00:59:45.701 --> 00:59:47.817
[GRUNTING]

995
00:59:52.861 --> 00:59:56.490
Velma. What's going on?
Why are you doing this?

996
00:59:56.701 --> 00:59:58.373
Our date wasn't that bad, was it?

997
00:59:58.581 --> 01:00:03.814
Why? To make them pay,
to make them all pay.

998
01:00:03.981 --> 01:00:08.736
Now, that I've rebuilt my staff,
no one can stop me.

999
01:00:16.541 --> 01:00:17.940
[COUGHING]

1000
01:00:25.981 --> 01:00:30.657
Well, there's another mystery solved,
huh, gang?

1001
01:00:31.221 --> 01:00:32.449
I got it.

1002
01:00:32.621 --> 01:00:34.213
Okay.

1003
01:00:35.421 --> 01:00:39.460
What in the world is going on?
Why is Velma doing this?

1004
01:00:39.941 --> 01:00:41.169
Oh, no.

1005
01:00:41.381 --> 01:00:44.134
You don't think my passions
drove her mad, do you?

1006
01:00:44.301 --> 01:00:46.690
I'm sure there's something bigger
than that going on.

1007
01:00:46.861 --> 01:00:48.089
I'll say.

1008
01:00:49.101 --> 01:00:53.617
Your friend has been possessed by
the spirit of the witch Wanda Grubwort.

1009
01:00:54.261 --> 01:00:58.812
Oh, great, my first love
and she's turned into an evil witch.

1010
01:00:58.981 --> 01:01:00.972
Join the club.

1011
01:01:09.061 --> 01:01:11.495
Yeah. Hee, hee, hee.

1012
01:01:11.661 --> 01:01:12.776
It was that staff.

1013
01:01:12.941 --> 01:01:14.260
[IMITATES EXPLOSION]

1014
01:01:14.421 --> 01:01:16.696
She must have found the pieces...

1015
01:01:16.861 --> 01:01:20.490
...that have been buried
all these many years.

1016
01:01:21.101 --> 01:01:23.535
Like, by any chance...

1017
01:01:23.701 --> 01:01:26.340
...did moonstones
play any part in this?

1018
01:01:26.901 --> 01:01:30.416
As soon as your friend touched one
of those rocks...

1019
01:01:30.581 --> 01:01:33.812
...the spirit of my evil ancestor
took hold of her...

1020
01:01:33.981 --> 01:01:37.257
...and compelled her to find the rest.

1021
01:01:37.421 --> 01:01:39.889
SCOOBY: For you, old lady.
- Oh.

1022
01:01:41.101 --> 01:01:44.411
So it's been Velma the entire time?

1023
01:01:44.621 --> 01:01:48.250
Like, zoinks.
It's been right under our noses.

1024
01:01:48.461 --> 01:01:50.850
<i>The evil spirit must have first taken</i>
<i>hold of her...</i>

1025
01:01:51.021 --> 01:01:53.012
<i>... when we found that stone</i>
<i>by the lake.</i>

1026
01:01:53.781 --> 01:01:57.820
And those creepy warts, it was like
she was actually turning into a witch.

1027
01:01:58.021 --> 01:01:59.374
Being burned at the stake...

1028
01:01:59.541 --> 01:02:02.339
<i>... would make me pretty freaked out</i>
<i>at the sight of fire too.</i>

1029
01:02:02.541 --> 01:02:05.419
And I bet she intentionally shorted out
the security console...

1030
01:02:05.581 --> 01:02:07.890
<i>... because she knew</i>
<i>we'd see her face.</i>

1031
01:02:08.461 --> 01:02:10.417
I can't believe we missed it.

1032
01:02:10.581 --> 01:02:13.459
I guess we were all too wrapped up
in our own little dramas...

1033
01:02:13.621 --> 01:02:15.976
...to catch the really big one going on.

1034
01:02:16.781 --> 01:02:17.770
[SIGHS]

1035
01:02:18.261 --> 01:02:23.460
So now that she has her powers back,
what's Wanda Grubwort going to do?

1036
01:02:23.621 --> 01:02:26.931
I fear that what she seeks
is the revenge...

1037
01:02:27.101 --> 01:02:30.377
...that has eluded her all these years.

1038
01:02:31.101 --> 01:02:32.853
Who cares about what she wants.

1039
01:02:33.021 --> 01:02:36.900
We gotta save Velma. Do you have
any idea where she would have gone?

1040
01:02:37.101 --> 01:02:39.695
Oh, probably to the caves
where she lived.

1041
01:02:39.861 --> 01:02:41.055
The caves?

1042
01:02:41.261 --> 01:02:43.855
But what about the irrigated
rudimentary claymations?

1043
01:02:44.061 --> 01:02:45.050
The what?

1044
01:02:45.221 --> 01:02:48.258
The entrances to the caves,
they're all underwater.

1045
01:02:48.421 --> 01:02:49.740
How would we get in?

1046
01:02:50.661 --> 01:02:52.970
You're in luck. I rent scuba gear.

1047
01:02:53.181 --> 01:02:55.775
I'll give you a good deal too.

1048
01:03:07.821 --> 01:03:09.732
Smile.

1049
01:03:50.701 --> 01:03:52.817
Zoinks.

1050
01:04:04.901 --> 01:04:06.698
FRED:
Lights.

1051
01:04:24.741 --> 01:04:25.730
Uh-oh.

1052
01:04:33.141 --> 01:04:34.733
VELMA [IN DISTORTED VOICE]:
Ah.

1053
01:04:34.901 --> 01:04:37.813
You've been a faithful servant.

1054
01:04:37.981 --> 01:04:42.736
And now I think you deserve
some playmates.

1055
01:04:42.901 --> 01:04:44.459
[BELLOWS]

1056
01:04:46.461 --> 01:04:48.497
She's making more of those things.

1057
01:04:55.421 --> 01:04:57.810
VELMA:
Rise, my slithering slaves.

1058
01:04:58.021 --> 01:05:01.377
Rise and serve your new master.

1059
01:05:06.261 --> 01:05:08.252
[GROWLING]

1060
01:05:08.621 --> 01:05:09.610
[GASPS]

1061
01:05:09.781 --> 01:05:11.976
Finally, we'll make them pay.

1062
01:05:12.141 --> 01:05:15.497
Make them rue the day
they set foot on our land.

1063
01:05:16.141 --> 01:05:18.575
Those things are gonna attack
everyone in town.

1064
01:05:18.741 --> 01:05:21.733
- We have to do something.
- What can we do?

1065
01:05:21.901 --> 01:05:25.371
Hey, Fred, I know this is usually
your department, but do you mind...?

1066
01:05:25.541 --> 01:05:28.294
- If you've got a plan, Shaggy, go for it.
- Okay.

1067
01:05:29.581 --> 01:05:33.130
Velma Dacey Dinkley,
you stop that this instant.

1068
01:05:34.181 --> 01:05:39.778
I told you,
Velma doesn't live here anymore.

1069
01:05:39.981 --> 01:05:42.336
That was your big idea, Shags?

1070
01:05:42.541 --> 01:05:45.738
Creatures, change of plans.

1071
01:05:45.941 --> 01:05:47.135
Get them.

1072
01:05:48.421 --> 01:05:50.332
SCOOBY:
Hold still.

1073
01:05:53.621 --> 01:05:55.179
Thank you. Aah!

1074
01:06:05.981 --> 01:06:06.970
Velma.

1075
01:06:07.141 --> 01:06:10.736
Velma, I know you're still in there.
I know you can hear me.

1076
01:06:12.661 --> 01:06:15.459
Okay, like, maybe you can't.

1077
01:06:19.941 --> 01:06:21.294
DAPHNE:
This is like biology class...

1078
01:06:21.461 --> 01:06:24.498
...except this time
the frogs are gonna dissect us.

1079
01:06:26.341 --> 01:06:28.491
Like, come on, V.
You gotta listen to me.

1080
01:06:28.661 --> 01:06:31.414
You're stronger than this thing
inside of you.

1081
01:06:31.621 --> 01:06:35.819
You're stronger
and you're smarter and you're cuter.

1082
01:06:36.661 --> 01:06:39.300
- [IN NORMAL VOICE] I am?
- That's right, V.

1083
01:06:39.461 --> 01:06:42.976
I think everything about you is cute.
Like the way...

1084
01:06:43.141 --> 01:06:45.780
...your pleated skirt ruffles
when you run from ghosts.

1085
01:06:45.981 --> 01:06:47.300
How... And even...

1086
01:06:47.461 --> 01:06:51.454
Even how you lose your glasses
at the most inopportune moments.

1087
01:06:51.621 --> 01:06:56.615
Yeah. Yeah, as a matter of fact,
that might be the cutest thing of all.

1088
01:06:57.501 --> 01:06:59.332
Shaggy?

1089
01:06:59.981 --> 01:07:02.256
- Help me.
- Yeah.

1090
01:07:02.461 --> 01:07:05.373
Yeah, listen, V.
You gotta fight this old witch.

1091
01:07:05.581 --> 01:07:06.570
- Okay.
- Okay?

1092
01:07:06.741 --> 01:07:09.539
Shaggy, I'll try. I'll try.

1093
01:07:09.701 --> 01:07:11.498
[IN DISTORTED VOICE]
No, you won't.

1094
01:07:12.581 --> 01:07:14.333
[SHAGGY SCREAMING]

1095
01:07:18.381 --> 01:07:22.818
Well, at least now I can finally say
I've been picked up by a girl.

1096
01:07:43.461 --> 01:07:45.656
See you, froggies.

1097
01:07:54.101 --> 01:07:56.171
FRED:
Run, run.

1098
01:08:05.461 --> 01:08:07.816
That ought to hold them for a while.
Come on.

1099
01:08:12.781 --> 01:08:15.136
Knock me down all you want,
Wanda Grubwort...

1100
01:08:15.341 --> 01:08:19.732
...but I'm not gonna let a couple of
stupid moonstones take my friend away.

1101
01:08:20.701 --> 01:08:22.931
Oh, wait, moon. Oh, that's it.

1102
01:08:23.861 --> 01:08:26.898
[SINGING]
<i>By the light of the silvery moon</i>

1103
01:08:27.061 --> 01:08:28.176
What is it? What are you...?

1104
01:08:28.341 --> 01:08:30.138
<i>By the light</i>

1105
01:08:30.301 --> 01:08:31.939
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
<i>Not the dark but the light</i>

1106
01:08:33.101 --> 01:08:35.376
<i>Of the silvery moon</i>

1107
01:08:35.541 --> 01:08:38.055
<i>Not the sun, but the moon</i>

1108
01:08:38.221 --> 01:08:40.132
<i>I want to spoon</i>

1109
01:08:40.301 --> 01:08:41.814
[IN DISTORTED VOICE]
No, you're mine.

1110
01:08:42.021 --> 01:08:46.253
- <i>To my honey I'll croon love's tune</i>
- [IN NORMAL VOICE] <i>Croon love's tune</i>

1111
01:08:46.861 --> 01:08:51.537
- <i>Oh, by the light of the silvery</i>
- <i>Light of the silvery</i>

1112
01:08:52.021 --> 01:08:54.410
VELMA: <i>Moon</i>
WANDA: Oh!

1113
01:08:54.581 --> 01:08:56.094
[GROANING]

1114
01:09:03.501 --> 01:09:04.570
It's a dead end.

1115
01:09:08.101 --> 01:09:10.057
I'm sorry, Daph.

1116
01:09:10.221 --> 01:09:11.734
I really was a jerk.

1117
01:09:11.941 --> 01:09:13.659
I'm sorry too, Fred.

1118
01:09:13.821 --> 01:09:16.733
I never should've tried
to make you jealous.

1119
01:09:17.621 --> 01:09:19.737
[MONSTERS ROARING]

1120
01:09:21.181 --> 01:09:25.891
Get out of me, Wanda Grubwort.

1121
01:09:28.821 --> 01:09:30.812
[WANDA SCREAMING]

1122
01:09:35.061 --> 01:09:39.373
Nothing can stop me now. Come.

1123
01:09:54.101 --> 01:09:55.978
SCOOBY:
Not so fast.

1124
01:09:56.181 --> 01:09:57.853
What? No.

1125
01:09:58.421 --> 01:10:01.572
Say goodbye, wicked witch.

1126
01:10:01.781 --> 01:10:06.616
No, no. Revenge was in my grasp.

1127
01:10:06.781 --> 01:10:09.056
And I would have gotten away
with it...

1128
01:10:09.221 --> 01:10:13.851
...if it wasn't for you meddling kids
and your rotten dog.

1129
01:10:14.021 --> 01:10:15.010
[GIGGLES]

1130
01:10:15.181 --> 01:10:19.094
Oh, no. No.

1131
01:10:20.101 --> 01:10:21.898
[SCREAMS]

1132
01:10:22.781 --> 01:10:24.772
[MONSTERS SLITHERING]

1133
01:10:30.261 --> 01:10:31.660
[FROGS CROAKING]

1134
01:10:35.301 --> 01:10:37.690
Shaggy did it. Come on.

1135
01:10:39.341 --> 01:10:41.093
VELMA:
Shaggy?

1136
01:10:42.421 --> 01:10:44.218
Is it over?

1137
01:10:48.141 --> 01:10:50.416
I think so, V.

1138
01:10:52.501 --> 01:10:54.571
Those things you said to me.

1139
01:10:56.421 --> 01:10:58.013
Did you really mean all of that?

1140
01:10:59.101 --> 01:11:01.057
Of course I did.

1141
01:11:01.261 --> 01:11:04.458
I've been trying to say it
ever since we got here.

1142
01:11:06.981 --> 01:11:09.017
Just kiss her already.

1143
01:11:09.501 --> 01:11:11.696
Oh, well, I...

1144
01:11:11.901 --> 01:11:14.335
Shaggy, just kiss me already.

1145
01:11:24.381 --> 01:11:25.814
SHAGGY:
Well, um...

1146
01:11:25.981 --> 01:11:27.539
That was, uh...

1147
01:11:28.341 --> 01:11:29.660
Yeah.

1148
01:11:30.661 --> 01:11:33.858
You know,
I don't know too much about chemistry.

1149
01:11:34.021 --> 01:11:35.852
I do, Shaggy.

1150
01:11:36.061 --> 01:11:41.215
And, well, there just wasn't any.

1151
01:11:41.381 --> 01:11:43.337
Yeah, I...

1152
01:11:44.101 --> 01:11:48.253
You know, maybe we're just better off
being friends.

1153
01:11:48.421 --> 01:11:50.889
You know what? Maybe we all are.

1154
01:11:51.061 --> 01:11:52.494
Yeah.

1155
01:11:53.461 --> 01:11:54.689
Phew.

1156
01:11:54.861 --> 01:11:58.376
THORNY: Well, kids, with the creature
gone, we have a ton of new applications.

1157
01:11:58.541 --> 01:12:00.213
Maybe more than we can handle.

1158
01:12:00.821 --> 01:12:03.289
- And it's all thanks to you guys.
- Aw.

1159
01:12:05.861 --> 01:12:08.500
Oh, that reminds me.

1160
01:12:10.981 --> 01:12:15.293
FRED: What?
- Something to show my appreciation.

1161
01:12:15.461 --> 01:12:18.214
- Ten thousand dollars?
- Uncle Thorny.

1162
01:12:18.381 --> 01:12:19.939
- Oh.
- Aw.

1163
01:12:22.141 --> 01:12:25.611
By the way, I took the liberty to set up
an appointment with my attorney...

1164
01:12:25.781 --> 01:12:27.453
...for you to discuss incorporating.

1165
01:12:28.101 --> 01:12:30.820
Thought that might help
with your future liability issues.

1166
01:12:30.981 --> 01:12:32.334
- Yeah.
- Oh, man.

1167
01:12:32.501 --> 01:12:35.254
- Shall we go play around?
SHAGGY: This is gonna be amazing, guys.

1168
01:12:35.421 --> 01:12:37.855
- So insane.
- Hey, you guys, I've got it.

1169
01:12:38.021 --> 01:12:40.171
We can be Mystery Incorporated.

1170
01:12:40.341 --> 01:12:42.297
- I love it.
- I can totally dig that.

1171
01:12:42.461 --> 01:12:43.780
Hey, Scooby, get a picture.

1172
01:12:43.981 --> 01:12:45.255
[LAUGHS]

1173
01:12:45.421 --> 01:12:46.774
FRED:
Everybody say, "Mystery Inc."

1174
01:12:46.981 --> 01:12:49.290
ALL:
Mystery Inc.

1175
01:12:49.461 --> 01:12:51.452
- Oh, my goodness.
- Guys, group hug.

1176
01:12:51.621 --> 01:12:53.418
- Okay.
- Okay, all right.

1177
01:12:53.581 --> 01:12:55.333
VELMA: Okay, Shaggy.
DAPHNE: Shaggy.

1178
01:12:55.501 --> 01:12:57.776
VELMA: Shaggy.
FRED: Okay...

1179
01:12:59.061 --> 01:13:01.291
All right. We'll celebrate.

1180
01:13:01.501 --> 01:13:02.490
All right. Bye, guys.

1181
01:13:02.661 --> 01:13:04.970
Not the hair, man. Not the hair.

1182
01:13:06.101 --> 01:13:07.170
[SIGHS]

1183
01:13:08.341 --> 01:13:09.933
[WHIMPERING]

1184
01:13:10.101 --> 01:13:12.092
[GRUNTING]

1185
01:13:25.221 --> 01:13:26.210
Don't worry, Scoob.

1186
01:13:26.901 --> 01:13:30.576
No matter what happens,
I'll always be here for you.

1187
01:13:30.781 --> 01:13:33.249
Oh, Shaggy.

1188
01:13:45.381 --> 01:13:47.417
[SINGING]
<i>When danger used to come around</i>

1189
01:13:47.581 --> 01:13:49.537
<i>I would fall right to the ground</i>

1190
01:13:49.701 --> 01:13:51.851
<i>It's true</i>

1191
01:13:53.901 --> 01:13:56.813
<i>But now that I can see your face</i>

1192
01:13:56.981 --> 01:14:01.657
<i>Well, I can stand up to anything</i>

1193
01:14:01.821 --> 01:14:04.494
<i>And how I cherish the times</i>

1194
01:14:04.661 --> 01:14:09.212
<i>When the sun shines on the two of us</i>

1195
01:14:09.621 --> 01:14:11.020
<i>But I don't mind going through</i>

1196
01:14:11.181 --> 01:14:16.301
<i>The bad times</i>
<i>Just as long as they're with you</i>

1197
01:14:16.861 --> 01:14:20.137
<i>Well, I can be scared with you</i>

1198
01:14:21.221 --> 01:14:23.496
<i>I can be alone with you</i>

1199
01:14:24.861 --> 01:14:28.979
<i>As long as I have your hand</i>
<i>To hold onto</i>

1200
01:14:29.141 --> 01:14:34.261
<i>I can be scared with you</i>

1201
01:14:34.421 --> 01:14:36.981
[CHORUS HUMMING]

1202
01:14:40.021 --> 01:14:43.730
<i>I can be scared with you</i>

1203
01:14:43.901 --> 01:14:49.180
<i>Oh, I can be scared</i>
<i>As long as I'm with you</i>

1204
01:14:51.861 --> 01:14:55.740
<i>I can do anything</i>

1205
01:14:55.901 --> 01:14:58.893
<i>I can do anything</i>

1206
01:14:59.061 --> 01:15:04.613
<i>As long as I'm with you</i>

1207
01:15:05.021 --> 01:15:07.012
[DISCO MUSIC PLAYING]

1208
01:15:19.181 --> 01:15:21.490
[SINGING]
<i>I can be scared with you</i>

